This article provides an update on the United States Government's response to the Haiti earthquake disaster that occurred on January 12, 2010. The government has mobilized resources and people to aid in the relief effort, with USAID taking the lead. Military personnel are playing a crucial role in supporting the humanitarian effort, including logistics and distribution of aid. The U.S. is coordinating with more than 30 nations and hundreds of NGOs to deliver food and water quickly throughout Haiti. The article also highlights key facts and examples of government actions in various areas, such as health/medical, airports/ports, safety/security, evacuation/rescues, food/water, adoptions/orphans, and assistance. It also provides information on how to support relief efforts and find information about friends and family in Haiti.